title: 'Confirm and Save Parsed CV'
api: 'POST /api/v1/cv-parse/confirm'
description: 'Confirm and save the parsed CV data to your profile'
---

## Endpoint

```
POST /api/v1/cv-parse/confirm
```

**Base URL**: `http://localhost:3000/api/v1`

<Note>This endpoint requires **authentication** and **Job Seeker role**.</Note>

## Authentication

Include the access token in the Authorization header:

```bash
Authorization: Bearer YOUR_ACCESS_TOKEN
```

## Description

Review the parsed CV data and confirm to save it to your profile. This creates or updates your JobSeekerProfile, Education, WorkExperience, and JobSeekerSkill records. You can modify any fields in the request body before confirming.

## Request Body

<ParamField body="personalInfo" type="object" required>
  Personal information including name and contact details.
</ParamField>

<ParamField body="personalInfo.firstName" type="string" required>
  First name of the job seeker.
</ParamField>

<ParamField body="personalInfo.lastName" type="string" required>
  Last name of the job seeker.
</ParamField>

<ParamField body="personalInfo.cvEmail" type="string" required>
  Email address from the CV.
</ParamField>

<ParamField body="personalInfo.phone" type="string" required>
  Phone number.
</ParamField>

<ParamField body="personalInfo.location" type="string" optional>
  Location/address.
</ParamField>

<ParamField body="personalInfo.linkedinUrl" type="string" optional>
  LinkedIn profile URL.
</ParamField>

<ParamField body="personalInfo.githubUrl" type="string" optional>
  GitHub profile URL.
</ParamField>

<ParamField body="personalInfo.portfolioUrl" type="string" optional>
  Portfolio website URL.
</ParamField>

<ParamField body="title" type="string" required>
  Job title (e.g., "Software Engineer").
</ParamField>

<ParamField body="summary" type="string" required>
  Professional summary.
</ParamField>

<ParamField body="education" type="array" required>
  Array of education entries.
</ParamField>

<ParamField body="workExperience" type="array" required>
  Array of work experience entries.
</ParamField>

<ParamField body="skills" type="array" required>
  Array of skills. Each skill has `name` and `verified` flag.
</ParamField>

<ParamField body="profile" type="object" required>
  Profile preferences and details.
</ParamField>

<ParamField body="profile.expectedSalary" type="number" optional>
  Expected salary.
</ParamField>

<ParamField body="profile.workPreference" type="string" optional>
  Work preference: ONSITE, REMOTE, HYBRID, ANY
</ParamField>

<ParamField body="profile.yearsOfExperience" type="number" optional>
  Years of experience.
</ParamField>

<ParamField body="profile.noticePeriod" type="number" optional>
  Notice period in days.
</ParamField>

<ParamField body="profile.availabilityStatus" type="string" optional>
  Availability status: OPEN_TO_WORK, NOT_LOOKING, PASSIVELY_LOOKING
</ParamField>

## Request Example

```json
{
  "personalInfo": {
    "firstName": "Amr",
    "lastName": "Ashraf Mubarak",
    "cvEmail": "amrrdev@gmail.com",
    "phone": "+20 120 456 2326",
    "location": "",
    "linkedinUrl": "linkedin.com/in/amramubarak",
    "githubUrl": "github.com/amrrdev",
    "portfolioUrl": null
  },
  "title": "Software Engineer",
  "summary": "Software Engineer with 1+ year of experience building scalable microservices and RESTful APIs using Node.js and NestJS.",
  "education": [
    {
      "institutionName": "Benha University",
      "degreeType": "BACHELOR",
      "fieldOfStudy": "Science in Computer Science",
      "startDate": "2022",
      "endDate": "2026",
      "isCurrent": false,
      "gpa": 3.6,
      "description": null
    }
  ],
  "workExperience": [
    {
      "companyName": "Linux Foundation Decentralized Trust",
      "jobTitle": "Software Engineer",
      "location": "Remote",
      "startDate": "2025-05-01",
      "endDate": "2025-07-01",
      "isCurrent": false,
      "description": "Developed a testing strategy for a decentralized trust solution..."
    }
  ],
  "skills": [
    { "name": "typescript", "verified": true },
    { "name": "node.js", "verified": true },
    { "name": "nestjs", "verified": true }
  ],
  "profile": {
    "expectedSalary": null,
    "workPreference": "REMOTE",
    "yearsOfExperience": 0.3,
    "noticePeriod": null,
    "availabilityStatus": "NOT_LOOKING"
  }
}
```

## Response

### Success Response (200 OK)

```json
{
  "success": true,
  "data": {
    "message": "Profile updated successfully from CV"
  },
  "message": "Success",
  "meta": {
    "timestamp": "2026-02-20T14:47:55.971Z",
    "path": "/cv-parse/confirm",
    "method": "POST"
  }
}
```

## Error Responses

### 400 Bad Request - Validation Errors

```json
{
  "success": false,
  "error": {
    "message": [
      "profile.workPreference must be one of the following values: ONSITE, REMOTE, HYBRID, ANY",
      "profile.yearsOfExperience must be a number conforming to the specified constraints",
      "profile.availabilityStatus must be one of the following values: OPEN_TO_WORK, NOT_LOOKING, PASSIVELY_LOOKING"
    ],
    "statusCode": 400,
    "timestamp": "2026-02-20T14:47:55.971Z",
    "path": "/cv-parse/confirm",
    "method": "POST",
    "details": "Bad Request"
  }
}
```

### 400 Bad Request - No Completed Parse Result

```json
{
  "success": false,
  "error": {
    "message": "No completed parse result to confirm",
    "statusCode": 400,
    "timestamp": "2026-02-20T14:00:00.000Z",
    "path": "/cv-parse/confirm",
    "method": "POST"
  }
}
```

## Complete CV Flow

<Steps>
  <Step title="Upload CV">Call POST /cv/presigned-url to get an upload URL</Step>
  <Step title="Upload File">Upload the file using PUT with the upload URL</Step>
  <Step title="Confirm Upload">Call POST /cv/confirm to trigger NLP parsing</Step>
  <Step title="Preview Data">Call GET /cv-parse/preview to see parsed results</Step>
  <Step title="Confirm & Save">Call POST /cv-parse/confirm to save to your profile</Step>
</Steps>

<Info>
  **What gets saved**: This endpoint saves the following to your profile: - JobSeekerProfile: title,
  summary, phone, cvEmail, location, social links, work preferences - Education: all education
  entries - WorkExperience: all work experience entries - JobSeekerSkill: all skills with verified:
  true flag
</Info>
</file>

<file path="docs/api-reference/cv/introduction.mdx">
---
title: Introduction
description: 'CV API - Upload, parse, and manage job seeker CVs'
---

# CV API

The CV API provides endpoints for uploading, parsing, and managing job seeker CVs.

## Base URL

```
http://localhost:3000/api/v1
```

## Endpoints Overview

| Method | Endpoint                | Description                    | Auth Required    |
| ------ | ----------------------- | ------------------------------ | ---------------- |
| POST   | `/cv/presigned-url`     | Request CV upload URL          | Yes (Job Seeker) |
| PUT    | `{uploadUrl}`           | Upload CV file to storage      | No (signed URL)  |
| POST   | `/cv/confirm`           | Confirm CV upload and parse    | Yes (Job Seeker) |
| GET    | `/cv/me`                | Get current CV info            | Yes (Job Seeker) |
| GET    | `/cv/me/download-url`   | Get CV download URL            | Yes (Job Seeker) |
| DELETE | `/cv/me`                | Delete current CV              | Yes (Job Seeker) |
| GET    | `/cv-parse/preview`     | Preview parsed CV data         | Yes (Job Seeker) |
| POST   | `/cv-parse/confirm`     | Confirm and save to profile    | Yes (Job Seeker) |

**CV Upload Flow:** Request URL -> Upload File -> Confirm Upload -> NLP Parsing

**CV Parse Flow:** Preview Parsed Data -> Confirm and Save to Profile

> **Note:** Skills extracted from CV have `verified: true` flag indicating they were parsed from
> the CV document.

See detailed documentation for each endpoint in the API Reference section.
</file>

